"title": "7622: disciples, characteristics of",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7622",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The content of discipleship is most clearly seen in the Christian's relationship to Jesus Christ. But this also affects a person's relationship to God the Father, the cross, the church and the world.</p>\n<h2>Disciples and their relationship to Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Coming to Christ and following him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:19\">MAT 4:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:28\">MAT 11:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark10:21\">MRK 10:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke18:16\">LUK 18:16</a></p>\n<h3>Receiving him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev3:20\">REV 3:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John1:12\">JHN 1:12</a></p>\n<h3>Learning from him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt11:29\">MAT 11:29</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt24:32\">MAT 24:32</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark13:28\">MRK 13:28</a></p>\n<h3>Lovingly obeying him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:15\">JHN 14:15</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Trusting him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John14:1\">JHN 14:1</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Confessing him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt10:38\">MAT 10:38</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:27\">LUK 14:27</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:38\">MRK 8:38</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:26\">LUK 9:26</a></p>\n<h3>Imitating him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor11:1\">1CO 11:1</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:21\">1PE 2:21</a></p>\n<h3>Reflecting him</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:16\">MAT 5:16</a></p>\n<h3>Abiding in him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:4\">JHN 15:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:66-John6:68\">JHN 6:66–6:68</a></p>\n<h2>Disciples and their relationship to God the Father</h2>\n<h3>True sons and daughters of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:44-Matt5:45\">MAT 5:44–5:45</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Discipleship and glorifying God</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:16\">MAT 5:16</a></p>\n<h2>Disciples and their relationship to the cross</h2>\n<h3>Self-denial</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:24\">MAT 16:24</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:34\">MRK 8:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:23\">LUK 9:23</a></p>\n<h2>Disciples and their relationship to the church</h2>\n<h3>Treating other Christians as family</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark3:34-Mark3:35\">MRK 3:34–3:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt18:15-Matt18:17\">MAT 18:15–18:17</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:12\">JHN 15:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John15:17\">JHN 15:17</a></p>\n<h2>Disciples and their relationship to the world</h2>\n<h3>They are to be active in the world but are to be distinct from it</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13\">MAT 5:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:14-Matt5:16\">MAT 5:14–5:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John17:11-John17:23\">JHN 17:11–17:23</a></p>\n<h3>They are to make other disciples</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt28:19\">MAT 28:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts1:8\">ACT 1:8</a></p>",
